	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is only two ways to get your defense up. The first, spend practice points on it. I'm not even sure this will work as some skills can only be practiced up so far. But those are mostly traid skill. <br><br>The best sure fire way to increase Defense is to get attacked and fight back! I have actually done what I am about to suggest, and it completely worked. If you have a close cleric friend, take him and find a zone that has light blue mobs, perferably animals, and and a relativly safe spot, and pull one to you and go at it with a weapon. When you've taken a good mount of damage, the cleric heals you back up to full. It will take a long time to raise your skill at level 32. I started doing this at level 25. We did it in EK at the gorge entrance pulling gorge hounds and such. <br><br>most of my melee skills were around 30ish. We spent about 3 hours real time doing this. When we were done, all my skills were double to triple thier scores. Now at 31, Dodge is maxed out at 75, as is piercing at 110. Defense and offense are in there 120, as there is a level cap, but will soon be maxed out. I've also started one handed blunt. You never know when your going to get a very nice weapon in either skill. I would have taken 2hb as well, but there are time limits. <br><br>When ever I'm in a group of 5 or more, I take every chance I can to melee. If it cons light blue or higher, and there are only 1-2 mobs, I fight it out. If you can, go to everfrost and see if anyone is soloing the Ice Giants. Ask them if they would mind you attacking the giant. Tell them what you are doing, that all you really want is a safe way to increase your skill. Who knows they may even group with you and split some coin. It's happened to me once. Made 30 some plat in coin and got to keep a few of the weapons.<br><br>The benifits of doing this are these: I'm harder to hit, and when I do get hit, I don't take as much damage. If mana is low, I can still be usefully by attacking a mob with a weapon, cause I will hit and do some damage. And some, is better then none. <br><br>Currently I am on the look out for some weapons that have a very high damage to attack ratio. As I get up in levels, it seems fighting is goiong to help out more and save mana for when I really need it. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
