	   <tr><td colspan=2>root and nuke is your technique for soloing .. yes.. this is true.. <br>but play with your aoe n pb spells as you get them.. learn what you can and cant get away with in ae.. and get to know a good group that knows how a wizzard can be used.. one thing about being a wizzard its hard work sometimes cause people dont understand what your capable of damage wise and more importantly ..&quot;how your capable of it&quot;.. by lvl 34ish.. youll start to &quot;kite&quot; start with a single.. and dont root but bond them.. (wiz area snare) and work them around til you get the hang of it.. the move to two and three and four.. most people stick with four.. &quot;quad kiting&quot; however if you get good enough you can do five.. or even six.. just takes practice..(make sure your stocked up on sow potions or have jboots to =P) i wouldnt recomend six til lvl 54 .. &quot;jylls&quot;.. spell is a great pb for this.. <br>this is normally how i play my wiz at lvl 55<br>group:<br>3 tanks (our group happens to be 2 warriors and a ranger.)<br>1 cleric<br>1 wiz (me)<br>1 druid <br>1 chanter (depending on how many tanks and style of fighting.. ae or single pull)<br><br>people ask... why a druid over a tank?<br>well thats where the power of a wiz comes in.. lets say im in a group in sebilis.. killin froggies...<br>aoe and pb spells will work GREAT here if your cleric knows their job.. and the druid does as well.<br>the druid is your backup healer.. he mainly dots assists wit aoes.. but heals as the cleric is watching the very important tanks<br>druids is your personal healer.. why do you need one? well because if you have one.. you can &quot;point blank or pb&quot; your way outta alot of jams and into a ton of good xp and loot.. and &quot;aoe&quot; your way as well.. <br>normally in seb the puller .. will bring about four at a time.. once he has the agro of the first mob.. i will stand near him and in between the other three casting a pb spell.. for about 565 dmg i believe it is.. this spell in general &quot;jylls static pulse&quot; is my pb of choice n spell of choice for more then one mob.. its a 3second casting time and 200 mana spell so you can cast over n over hitting each mob for the alot dmg of the spell ... yes.. you are gonna get hit.. but while your buffs are up from the cleric.. and you have around 2k hit points which you will .. the druid now watches your health.. and heals you.. the tanks work there way to you one at a time assisting each other while the cleric heals them.. VERY affective way of fighting .. some people say well what happens if the healers are both agroed on.. never seen this.. typically its possible.. but the fight isnt gonna last long with you hiting for 1k every 7 seconds.. ive only been killed 1 time EVER fighting this way.. <br>now the problem with this tatic is.. well two problems..<br>1. groups dont understand pulling more then singles.. they keep it small.. cause they get a lil jumpy..if this is the case your in the wrong group.. you are capable of much much more..with ease.. finding tanks n a cleric that understand how a wiz is supposed to work is rare in this game.. i happen to have found a group of individuals that know..and quite frankly they trust me as well.. <br>2. if there is a chanter in the group.. he will more then likely just mez the adds.. and you will singlularly nuke for dd not using you aoe or pb at all.. i do group with one chanter alot.. whose very good at what he does.. and the game in general.. when hes around we fight this way.. when hes not around its the other way<br><br>these tatics work extremely well both ways.. but the pb aoe group for mob killing is much more efficient for loot and xp.. <br>this method takes time to establish..you need to find 3 tanks a druid and a cleric that your going to play with ALOT and get to know this style of fighting.. thats the work.. but give it a shot.. find people that understand and work with them.. <br>..be careful trying aoe n pb with out a second healer.. shaman or druid.. or whatever.. the cleric will have to work to hard.. causing failure in the group..and your group may get a lil pissed.. make sure you have the right group for this..<br>good luck whatever you do!!! <br>taygarr <br>wiz of the 55th season<br>the seventh hammer<br><br>&nbsp;<br>WIZROG!!!!!!!!</td></tr>
